<title>USA: Emerson Electric names Berges vice chairman.</title>
<headline>Emerson Electric names Berges vice chairman.</headline>
<dateline>ST. LOUIS 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Emerson Electric Co on Tuesday said James Berges was elected vice chairman and a director of the company.</p>
<p>Berges, 49, will have responsibility for three of the company's businesses: electric motors and appliance components, electronics, and industrial components and equipment, the company said.</p>
<p>Berges joined Emerson in 1976 and has held a number of key management positions.</p>
<p>Emerson shares rose 1-3/8 to 46-3/8 Tuesday.</p>
<p>((Chicago newsdesk, 312-408-8787))</p>
